body:
Files/symbols implementing entrypoints from JS into keyed Load IC:
- src/builtins/builtins-ic-gen.cc:
  Builtins::Generate_KeyedLoadIC(), Generate_KeyedLoadIC_Megamorphic(), Generate_KeyedLoadIC_PolymorphicName(), Generate_KeyedLoadICTrampoline(), Generate_KeyedLoadICBaseline(), Generate_EnumeratedKeyedLoadIC[Baseline](). Each delegates to AccessorAssembler methods.
- src/ic/accessor-assembler.cc:
  AccessorAssembler::GenerateKeyedLoadIC(), GenerateKeyedLoadIC_Megamorphic(), GenerateKeyedLoadIC_PolymorphicName(), GenerateKeyedLoadICTrampoline(), GenerateKeyedLoadICBaseline(), GenerateEnumeratedKeyedLoadIC[Baseline]().
  AccessorAssembler::KeyedLoadIC(const LoadICParameters*, LoadAccessMode), KeyedLoadICGeneric, KeyedLoadICPolymorphicName implement the IC control flow for keyed loads.
- src/ic/ic.cc:
  RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_KeyedLoadIC_Miss) is the runtime miss handler. KeyedLoadIC class methods implement feedback update and handler selection: KeyedLoadIC::Load, KeyedLoadIC::LoadName, KeyedLoadIC::RuntimeLoad, KeyedLoadIC::UpdateLoadElement, KeyedLoadIC::LoadElementHandler, KeyedLoadIC::LoadElementPolymorphicHandlers. Also helpers computing load mode for elements: GetNewKeyedLoadMode, GetUpdatedLoadModeForMap, AllowConvertHoleElementToUndefined, AllowReadingHoleElement.
- Interface descriptors (call conv): src/codegen/interface-descriptors.h and per-arch in codegen/*/interface-descriptors-*-inl.h define KeyedLoad{,WithVector,Baseline} descriptors used by builtins.
explanation: This entry concentrates the concrete entrypoints from JS into the Keyed Load IC: baseline/interpreter/builtin stubs route to AccessorAssembler methods, while runtime miss leads to KeyedLoadIC::Load. These functions are the starting points to understand fast paths for a[i] and their control flow.
